{"word":"δαιδάλλω","slug":"δαιδάλλω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δαιδάλλω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:δαίδαλος'><el>δαίδαλος</el></a>\n<p/><i>to work cunningly, deck</i> or <i>inlay with curious arts, to embellish</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>δεδαιδαλμένος</el>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/>"}]}